Please update it to fail and we will reopen the ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130703" author="johan1" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 15:44:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;screenshot with eclipse console, firefox output and rendered html&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130707" author="johan1" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 15:47:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Somehow I cannot reopen the issue (there is no button to do so). I attached a screenshot where you can see the problem. I do not know why the quickstart seems to work on your computer. Since it does not have the getResourceSettings().setParentFolderPlaceholder() it actually cannot work. Maybe the copy on your workstation got mixed up with the quickstart from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4141&quot; title=&quot;Automatic Linking in base page broken&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4141&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4141&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130709" author="johan1" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 15:52:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Andrea can you confirm the issue with the attached quickstart?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130712" author="mgrigorov" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 15:55:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I test with trunk and you with 1.5.1.&lt;br/&gt;
Igor fixed this problem with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4126&quot; title=&quot;Automatic Image Linking broken for images in base packages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4126&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4126&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130714" author="johan1" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 15:59:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see,  thanks. Vigor&apos;s comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4126&quot; title=&quot;Automatic Image Linking broken for images in base packages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4126&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4126&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; sounded more like a this &quot;not-a-bug&quot; response.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130766" author="johan1" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 17:00:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, I tested it myself with trunk. Works, BUT: Vigor now sets a default value (:&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; for parentFolderPlaceholder. This renders the JavaDoc comment &quot;Note that by default the placeholder string is &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;null&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; and thus will not allow to access parent folders. That is by purpose and for security reasons (see Wicket-1992).&quot; wrong. Does this now somehow affect &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-1992&quot; title=&quot;SharedResourceRequestTarget allows access to almost arbitrary files under WEB-INF.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-1992&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-1992&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130838" author="ivaynberg" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 18:09:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;most of the sensitive config files reside directly in WEB-INF dir, i now by default forbid access to it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130841" author="ivaynberg" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 18:13:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;seems to me this is a much better fix to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-1992&quot; title=&quot;SharedResourceRequestTarget allows access to almost arbitrary files under WEB-INF.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-1992&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-1992&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. most devs would probably set the parent placeholder without even thinking that it would enable access to WEB-INF dir, thus not really fixing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-1992&quot; title=&quot;SharedResourceRequestTarget allows access to almost arbitrary files under WEB-INF.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-1992&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-1992&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. this way, we have the best of both worlds out of the box.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130854" author="johan1" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 18:27:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree. just wanted to check back. thanks Igor!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
